Miscellaneous Highlights: Quinton de Kock scored the highest score of his ICC Men's Cricket World Cup career in Mumbai
De Kock ended his ODI career with 6770 runs at an average of 45.74 and a strike rate of 96.64, setting the standard for South Africa and racking up 21 centuries
Others: Josh Hazlewood and Mitchell Starc struck twice in the semi-final
Temba Bavuma departed for a duck at the end of the first over of the semi-final
Removing Quinton De Kock early was crucial for Australia's eventual success
De Kock's South Africa career is far from over with a T20 World Cup on the horizon in 2024
